## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

Lib version: 3.9.0

## Steps To Reproduce

`getSheetValues()` is [defined as](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/master/index.d.ts#L1197):
```
	/**
	 * return all rows as sparse array
	 */
	getSheetValues(): Row[];
```

So one would expect a `Row` type to be returned.

## The expected behaviour:

However reviewing the [code for this function](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs/blob/master/lib/doc/worksheet.js#L444):
```
  // return all rows as sparse array
  getSheetValues() {
    const rows = [];
    this._rows.forEach(row => {
      if (row) {
        rows[row.number] = row.values;
      }
    });
    return rows;
  }
```

A plain array is being returned instead.

## Possible solution (optional, but very helpful):

Update type definition to

```typescript
	/**
	 * return all rows as sparse array
	 */
	getSheetValues(): Cell[][];

```

